# Instructis — Next.js 14+ App Router project rules

Follow these rules for every file you create or modify in this project.

## Folder structure

- `app/api/v1/[resource]/route.ts` — HTTP route handlers only (list/create)
- `app/api/v1/[resource]/[id]/route.ts` — Resource by ID (get/update/delete)
- `services/[resource].service.ts` — Business logic
- `repositories/[resource].repository.ts` — Prisma queries only
- `lib/middlewares/` — withAuth, withRole, withValidation, withRateLimit
- `lib/utils/api-response.ts` — Standardised ApiResponse helper
- `lib/utils/errors.ts` — AppError, NotFoundError, ForbiddenError, ValidationError
- `lib/utils/catchAsync.ts` — Async error wrapper for all routes
- `lib/validations/[resource].schema.ts` — Zod schemas
- `types/` — Global TypeScript types

## Layer rules

- **route.ts**: No business logic. Only call withAuth, withRole, withValidation, then delegate to service. Always wrap with catchAsync.
- **service**: No Prisma imports. No HTTP/Next.js imports. Only business logic and calls to repository.
- **repository**: Only Prisma queries. No business logic. No service imports.
- **lib/**: Infrastructure only. Auth config, Prisma client, Zod schemas, utilities.

## Route pattern (every route must follow this exactly)

```ts
export const GET = catchAsync(async (req, { params }) => {
  const session = await withAuth(req);
  withRole(session, "ROLE");
  const data = await someService.method();
  return ApiResponse.success(data);
});
```

## ApiResponse shape

Always use ApiResponse; never return raw `Response.json`.

- `ApiResponse.success(data, message?, meta?)` → 200
- `ApiResponse.created(data, message?)` → 201
- `ApiResponse.error(message, status?)` → 400
- `ApiResponse.unauthorized()` → 401
- `ApiResponse.forbidden()` → 403
- `ApiResponse.notFound()` → 404

## Error handling

- Always throw AppError subclasses from service/repository layers; never return error objects.
- catchAsync catches all thrown errors and maps them to ApiResponse.error automatically.
- Never use try/catch inside route handlers.

## Validation

- All request bodies validated with `withValidation(req, schema)` using Zod.
- Schemas live in `lib/validations/[resource].schema.ts`.
- Never access `req.json()` directly in route handlers.

## Auth

- Auth: Better Auth with Prisma adapter.
- Session check: `withAuth(req)` — throws 401 if no session.
- Role check: `withRole(session, ...roles)` — throws 403 if insufficient role.
- Roles are strings: `"STUDENT"` | `"FACULTY"` | `"ADMIN"` (compared case-insensitively with DB role).

## General

- All API routes are versioned under `/api/v1/`.
- Webhooks live under `/api/webhooks/` outside versioning.
- Never put business logic in route.ts.
- Never import Prisma directly in services.
- Never import Next.js headers/cookies in services or repositories.
- Pagination always returns `{ data, meta: { total, page, limit, totalPages } }`.
